CEO Spark New Zealand
Auckland, Auckland, New Zealand
Summary
We’re living in a time of exponential disruption, where technology
advancement is providing the opportunity for us to operate in ways
we never imagined to create value. Conversely if we don’t face the
reality of this head on, we expose our business to risk.
As business leaders we need to adapt to the pace of change,
creating an environment for our people to build the skills and adopt
the practices that will enable them to flourish. Creating teams that
bring together different generations, experiences and skills from
multi-disciplines and harness their creativity to deliver world class
experiences for our customers.
Now more than ever we need to have our eyes up and out, learning
as individuals and as organisations, so we can bring the best ideas
to bear in New Zealand as well as learning from the many great
kiwis.
I have had a diverse career working across executive positions
in different industries including professional services, FMCG,
telecommunications and digital technology, in both New Zealand and
Australia.
I was appointed to Chief Executive of Spark on 1 July 2019, following
a number of executive roles over six years in Spark. Previous roles
include Customer Director, Chief Executive of Spark Digital for 2
years, and Chief Financial Officer for Spark for 3 years.
I’m passionate about mentoring women in business, a member of
Global Women and OnBeingBold an online collective developed
by women for women. OnBeingBold has been created to capture
and share the personal life journeys of prominent New Zealand
business women so that others can be reassured that the squiggly
line connecting home life and careers is anything but straight-
forward.
  Page 1 of 4
   
Prior to joining Spark as the CFO, I worked for 12 years with the Lion
Group, Australasia’s largest beverages group.
